The user updates his self-description as follows: I’m drawn to alternative/new‑wave/post‑punk records — angular guitars, propulsive, slightly off‑kilter rhythms, layered synth textures and moody, intimate vocal delivery; production that creates space, tension and sonic character rather than polishing everything flat. I prefer albums where songs have distinct identities, reveal details on repeat listens, and sustain a cohesive mood or edge that rewards full‑disc play. From earlier tastes I retain a liking for emotional grit, strong songwriting, clear instrument separation and careful mastering/physical pressings that preserve nuance. I dislike over‑polished arena‑AOR formulae and glossy “greatest hits” homogenization: bombastic, interchangeable choruses or production that flattens dynamics and erases individual performance character. I avoid releases that favor safety and sheen over textural interest and individuality.

